text: how to get everything after last slash in a URL?
How can I extract whatever follows the last slash in a URL in python?
For example, these URLs should return the following:

code:
URL: http://www.test.com/TEST1
returns: TEST1

URL: http://www.test.com/page/TEST2
returns: TEST2

URL: http://www.test.com/page/page/12345
returns: 12345

text: I've tried urlparse, but that gives me the full path filename, such as page/page/12345.
